      • uploadStarted

        public void uploadStarted(com.vaadin.ui.Upload.StartedEvent event)
        Determines if the file's extension of the file being uploaded is within the accepted file extension format and validates the existence of the file. If no file is uploaded or invalid file type is detected, display an appropriate error message.

        The method also initialises the progress bar's value and set its visibility to true.

        If the size of file being uploaded is greater than the database would allow, cancel upload event and show the appropriate error to user.

        Specified by:
        uploadStarted in interface com.vaadin.ui.Upload.StartedListener
        Parameters:
        event - the StartedEvent object defined by the Upload class
